  "bodyLines": [
    "you will be responsible for suggesting features and business kpis and often stepping into product manager, designer, or infra-engineer shoes. we will meet once a day, deploy daily, and communicate using slack.",
    "this is a long-term contract position (100-140 hours a month)",
    "what you’ll do",
    "design and implement software solutions, from front-end components to backend infrastructure",
    "collaborate with founders, physicians, and other engineers to share a user-centric health platform",
    "build consumer and practitioner features (mobile and web) such as ai coaching/insights, signup flows, data visualization, and automations",
    "own technical decisions and contribute to the company’s product strategy",
    "you’re a great fit if you have",
    "passion towards helping humans live a healthier life",
    "3+ experience as a software engineer with a focus on full stack development",
    "experience with react, typescript, ruby on rails, claude ai, aws, tailwind, ios & android",
    "have worked at an early-stage healthcare startup",
    "comfort working in a rapidly-evolving specialty",
    "our promise to you",
    "you’ll do good - sleep is fundamental to life: it improves our mental well-being, physical health, performance, and energy. we’re reinventing healthcare and helping the 70 million americans suffering from poor sleep, and you’ll be pivotal in making this happen.",
    "you’ll have fun - we’re early in our journey. you’ll experience tons of personal and professional growth with founders who are enthusiastic to make this vision a reality",
    "you’ll sleep well - we work hard, but also make sure to recharge. every great dream begins with a dreamer, and every great dreamer needs to be a good sleeper."
  ],
